Finance Executive job
in Singapore Singapore SG 11 Biopolis
Job Ref:
15157
COUNTRY:
United States
CITY:
Singapore Singapore SG 11 Biopolis
EMPLOYER:
INDUSTRY:
Finance
Job Code : 15157
Location : Singapore Singapore SG 11 Biopolis Way, Helios, #12-07/08
Category : Finance
Career Level : Experienced (Non-Manager)
Job Type : Full Time
Job Description :
Position Summary:
This position reports to the Finance Manager and has responsibility over Accounts Receivables, Accounts Payable, General Ledger and inter-company.
Key Responsibilities:
• Ensure prompt collection of Accounts Receivables, follow up with customers and coordinate with the Service team to resolve collection issues where appropriate
• Update accounts receivable receipts and perform credit hold per necessary
• Maintain accounts receivable customer data, issue debit and credit notes
• Process and validate claims from local Singapore staff upon approval by reporting managers
• Support Finance Manager in preparing crossed charges from / to related companies
• Ensure all office bills and expenses are duly paid to vendors, utilities and suppliers to ensure smooth operation
• Assist in Month End Closing
• Prepare monthly netting payments and receipts and reconciliation of inter-company transactions
• Maintain Fixed Asset and Prepayments
• Prepare and submit quarterly GST
• Prepare GL journal entries and input to accounting system
• Prepare monthly audit schedules and other reports as required
• Upload monthly financial reports to Hyperion financial management system
• Liaise with external auditors, and tax agent on company matters and Year End Audit
Minimum Requirements/Qualifications:
• Diploma in Accountancy, ACCA level 2 or equivalent
• 2 - 4 years of commercial accounting experience, with exposure in AR, AP and GL
• Proficient in MS Office Application. Knowledge of Syspro and Hyperion Financial Management (HFM) will be added advantage
• Detail oriented, independent and positive working attitude
• Hands on, able to take initiatives and work under pressure to meet deadlines
• Ability to start work immediately or within short notice period
This role will be remunerated based on local package .
(We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified)
Post Date:
04/29/2014
